{"body": "I think I'm a bit late here, but still: if you add timestamps when *changing* a table rather than creating it, NOT NULL fields need a default value. This migration used to work, and now fails because of this change:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nclass AddTimestampsToMyDearestTable < ActiveRecord::Migration\r\n  def change\r\n    change_table(:some_table) do |t|\r\n      t.timestamps\r\n    end\r\n  end\r\nend\r\n```\r\nIs that intentional? Is there a workaround?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4256983", "created_at": "2012-03-01T12:12:43Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/3334#issuecomment-4256983", "updated_at": "2012-03-01T12:12:43Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 3334, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/bzanchet", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/db9d3850381c196b2916e25a1e9016c0?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F4fa04fbc0b0ce68711f7550ce6113720.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet/received_events", "gravatar_id": "db9d3850381c196b2916e25a1e9016c0", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "bzanchet", "type": "User", "id": 8005, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bzanchet/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5238378fbd3543c15100fe92"}, "id": 4256983, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/3334"}
